author: craigmcc
msg: Add the ability to optionally specify an MBeanServer domain in which
object names for these MBeans should be created.

author: craigmcc
msg: Add the notion of a "group" on the <mbean> element, which allows you to
classify ManagedBean instances, and add a way to ask the registry for all
ManagedBeans that belong to a particular group.
In Tomcat, for instance, this will allow you to satisfy queries like "find
me all the ManagedBean definitions for implementations of the
'org.apache.catalina.Valve' interface".

author: craigmcc
msg: Add a demonstration / test program that illustrates using modeler to
manage a "fake" set of managed resources modeled after the top level
components of Catalina in Tomcat 4.

author: craigmcc
msg: Major updates to work around some nasty problems in the JMX RI:
* If there are no attribute change notification event listeners
registered, calling ModelMBean.setAttribute() causes an
exception
* AttributeChangeNotificationListener does not properly process
a null second argument (signifying an interest in all attributes)
* RequiredModelMBean does not correctly deal with attributes (i.e.
JavaBeans properties) of primitive Java types.
These problems have been addressed by including our own implementation of
the ModelMBean interface that behaves correctly.
